<h2 id="data-science">Data Science</h2>

<h3 id="modelling-the-impact-of-contact-tracing-apps-in-containing-the-covid-19-virus">Modelling the Impact of Contact-tracing Apps in Containing the COVID-19 Virus</h3>
<p><a href="https://github.com/christopheberle/covid-percolation"><img src="https://img.shields.io/badge/GitHub-View_on_GitHub-blue?logo=GitHub" alt="View on GitHub" /></a>
<a href="https://github.com/christopheberle/covid-percolation/blob/master/Covid-Percolation.ipynb"><img src="https://img.shields.io/badge/Jupyter-Open_Notebook-blue?logo=Jupyter" alt="Open Notebook" /></a>
<a href="https://arxiv.org/pdf/2004.07237.pdf"><img src="https://img.shields.io/badge/PDF-Read_Paper-blue?logo=adobe-acrobat-reader&amp;logoColor=white" alt="Read Paper" /></a></p>

<p><strong>Abstract</strong></p>
<div style="text-align: justify">I investigate a percolation model for the ability of contact-tracing programmes to contain the COVID-19 virus proposed by Bulchandani et al. in a 2020 paper. Numerical results are discussed and related to the current epidemic situation.</div>
<p><br /></p>
<center><img src="assets/img/infection-graph-tracing.svg" /></center>

