<h3 id="predicting-monthly-wildfires-in-the-us">Predicting monthly Wildfires in the US</h3>
<p><a href="https://github.com/christopheberle/us-wildfires"><img src="https://img.shields.io/badge/GitHub-View_on_GitHub-blue?logo=GitHub" alt="View on GitHub" /></a>
<a href="https://github.com/christopheberle/us-wildfires/blob/main/us-wildfires.md"><img src="https://img.shields.io/badge/RMarkdown-Open_Notebook-blue?logo=R" alt="Open Notebook" /></a></p>

<p><strong>Abstract</strong></p>
<div style="text-align: justify">In this notebook I am exploring hierarchical Bayesian models in PyMC3 in order to predict the number of wildfires in the US in the future. I will build a Log-Normal-Poisson model which accurately predicts the number of wildfires within a \(1\sigma\)-uncertainty.</div>
<p><br /></p>
<center><img src="assets/img/us-wildfires.png" /></center>

